UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '步道入口牌坊',
  name_en = 'Trail Entrance Archway',
  body = '<p>The Trail Entrance Archway stands at the main entrance of Shancheng Trail on Zhongxing Road in Yuzhong District, a stone archway combining traditional Ba-Yu architectural style with modern urban wayfinding. It features a four-pillar, three-bay structure in blue-gray stone, with gilded characters "山城步道" (Shancheng Trail) engraved on the crossbeam and couplets depicting old Chongqing street life carved on the flanking pillars—solemn, classical, and highly recognizable. Behind the archway begins the trail''s core uphill section, where stone steps wind upward along the mountainside, with old residences and new viewing platforms alternating on both sides. The moment you pass beneath the archway, you officially enter the time corridor of Shancheng Trail. A small plaza in front of the archway features a trail map and historical introduction panels, making it the first stop for visitors to understand the full route and plan their walk. The archway itself is a popular photo spot—especially at dusk when warm lights illuminate the carved characters against the layered silhouette of mountain-city buildings behind.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_mountain_trails_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '厚庐',
  name_en = 'Houlu Residence',
  body = '<p>Houlu Residence is a historically significant Republic-era building along the middle section of Shancheng Trail, originally built in the 1930s–40s during the War of Resistance as a private mansion of a military-political official. The two-story brick-and-wood structure faces north and is built against the hillside, with a blue-brick facade, traditional gray-tile roof, clean eave lines, and a portico supported by square pillars—reflecting the East-meets-West architectural style of the Republic era, combining the solid simplicity of traditional Ba-Yu dwellings with the geometric order of Western architecture. The name "Houlu" derives from the Chinese saying "thick virtue carries all things," and the stone plaque above the doorway remains well-preserved. The interior retains original wooden staircases, latticed windows, and period furnishings, offering a time-travel experience back to the wartime era. Several other contemporary buildings surround Houlu, forming a relatively complete Republic-era architectural cluster. As a key node in Shancheng Trail''s historical fabric, Houlu is not just a building but a microcosm of Chongqing''s memory as the wartime capital.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_mountain_trails_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '悬空栈道',
  name_en = 'Suspended Cliffside Walkway',
  body = '<p>The Suspended Cliffside Walkway is the most visually striking and experiential section of Shancheng Trail, built cantilevered off the cliff face in Yuzhong District. It extends over 100 meters with a width of 1.5 to 2 meters, with sections paved in transparent glass, revealing the vertical cliff drop of tens of meters below and the layered rooftops of the old town—an experience of pure visual thrill. The walkway uses steel beams as its skeleton, with anti-corrosion wood and tempered glass as surface materials, and stainless steel railings with wire mesh that minimize visual obstruction while ensuring safety. Walking along, one side is the solid mountain rock face, the other an abruptly open panorama—distant views of the Yangtze River and the South Bank skyline, close-up views of the dense gray-tiled rooftops and crisscrossing stone alleys of Shancheng Lane''s old quarter. On clear days, sunlight refracts through the glass panels in dappled patterns, creating a fascinating contrast with the old-town atmosphere below. At dusk, it is a prime spot to watch sunset glow illuminate the Yangtze, as warm orange light intertwines with the mountain-city skyline, forming a three-dimensional landscape painting unique to Chongqing.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_mountain_trails_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '仁爱荒野剧场',
  name_en = 'Ren''ai Wilderness Theater',
  body = '<p>Ren''ai Wilderness Theater is located on the upper section of Shancheng Trail, on the site of the former Ren''ai Church. After a thoughtful redesign, it has become an open-air theater blending historical ruins with wild aesthetic sensibility. The preserved remnants of the old church serve as a backdrop—stone walls covered in vines and moss, where the mottled marks of time contrast with and complement new plant growth. The center features a semicircular terraced stone seating area accommodating about 100 people, with a simple stage built from reclaimed wood and stone. The overall design is rugged and unadorned yet reveals carefully curated artistic intention at every turn. Native wildflowers and ornamental grasses surround the theater—lush and fragrant in spring and summer, evoking a melancholy poetry of bare branches in autumn and winter. Small concerts, poetry readings, theatrical performances, and outdoor screenings are held here regularly, and the space often becomes a spontaneous gathering spot for street artists and creative souls. Even on days without performances, simply sitting in this ruin-garden listening to wind and birdsong while gazing at the mountain-city skyline is enough to feel the unique cultural warmth and romantic undertone of Chongqing.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_mountain_trails_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '轨道李子坝站1号出口',
  name_en = 'Metro Liziba Station Exit 1',
  body = '<p>Metro Liziba Station Exit 1 is located on the side of the station building facing the Jialing River, serving as the primary entrance for visitors to experience the train-through-building marvel up close. Following the signs from inside the station to Exit 1, the moment you push open the glass doors and look up, you can see Line 2 trains gliding through the residential building overhead, just an arm''s length away. The engine sound and laundry hanging from residents'' windows create a fascinating coexistence. Simple guideboards and marked photo spots outside the exit indicate the best shooting angles and approximate train schedules. Many visitors linger here waiting for the perfect moment a train passes through, pressing the shutter to capture this urban wonder. The exit connects directly to Liziba Zheng Street, with steps leading down to the observation platform, making it the natural starting point for exploring the entire attraction.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_liziba_monorail_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '李子坝观景平台',
  name_en = 'Liziba Observation Platform',
  body = '<p>The Liziba Observation Platform is located on the Binjiang Road side of the Jialing River opposite Liziba Station. It was specially built by the Yuzhong District government in 2017 to provide a safe, spacious shooting space for the growing number of visitors. Covering approximately 1,500 square meters, the platform features a cantilevered steel structure extending several meters toward the Jialing River, offering an extremely open view. Looking up from here, the scene of Line 2 trains passing through the 6th to 8th floors of the residential building is fully visible—the best position for the classic train-through-building shot. Colorful graffiti and marked photo spots on the platform floor indicate recommended distances for shooting. The platform is equipped with sunshades, seating, drinking water facilities, and an electronic display showing real-time train arrival information. During holidays, the platform is packed with visitors and cameras, making it one of Chongqing''s most popular internet-famous spots.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_liziba_monorail_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '岩之魂浮雕文化墙',
  name_en = 'Spirit of Rock Relief Culture Wall',
  body = '<p>The Spirit of Rock Relief Culture Wall is located on the hillside retaining slope next to the Liziba Observation Platform—a large relief art group created on the existing retaining wall surface. The relief spans over 100 meters in length and several meters in height, with Chongqing''s unique landscape and cultural history as its creative thread. Classic Ba-Yu imagery—stilt houses, stone-paved roads, riverside piers, boat trackers, and old city gates—are layered and carved into the rock face. From afar it resembles an unfolded giant scroll; up close, rich details emerge: an old man carrying water, children at play, fishing boats rowing on the river—each scene vividly recreating old Chongqing''s street life. The relief combines realistic and impressionistic techniques, with bold, powerful lines and distinct light-and-shadow layers that produce different visual effects under varying sunlight. The wall not only beautifies the otherwise plain slope but also adds a cultural immersion experience for visitors waiting for trains, making it an unmissable artistic highlight of the Liziba area.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_liziba_monorail_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '文旅服务中心',
  name_en = 'Cultural Tourism Service Center',
  body = '<p>D拼装模型等特色商品。多媒体体验区则通过大屏播放李子坝轻轨建设历程纪录片和360度全景影像，让游客了解这一工程奇迹背后的故事。中心还提供行李寄存和无障碍通道服务，是游览李子坝的第一站和最佳补给点。 The Cultural Tourism Service Center is located near the Liziba Observation Platform, serving as the core supporting facility for the entire Liziba train-through-building attraction. The center features a modern, clean glass-curtain-wall exterior that creates an interesting contrast with the surrounding old mountain-city streets. Inside, it has four functional zones: a visitor information desk, rest area, cultural merchandise display area, and multimedia experience area. The information desk is staffed with bilingual (Chinese-English) personnel providing attraction maps, train schedules, and nearby dining recommendations. The rest area offers comfortable seating and free drinking water for visitors waiting between train pass-throughs. The merchandise area sells train-through-building-themed souvenirs including fridge magnets, postcards, hand-drawn maps, and 3D assembly models. The multimedia area plays documentaries about the construction of Liziba Metro and 360-degree panoramic footage on large screens, letting visitors understand the story behind this engineering marvel. The center also provides luggage storage and barrier-free access, making it the ideal first stop and supply point.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_liziba_monorail_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '巴渝旧闻馆',
  name_en = 'Ba-Yu Old News Gallery',
  body = '<p>The Ba-Yu Old News Gallery is a distinctive cultural venue within the Liziba train-through-building attraction, themed around modern Chongqing newspapers and journalism. Through physical exhibits, illustrated panels, and multimedia interactives, it presents a century of evolution in Chongqing''s press and public opinion—from the late Qing and early Republic to the reform and opening-up era. The gallery houses a collection of original and reprinted old newspapers, including historically significant titles such as Chongqing Daily, Xin Shu Bao, and Ta Kung Pao, whose front pages record major historical moments of Chongqing as wartime capital, industrial hub, and municipality. An "Old Papers, New Read" interactive station lets visitors browse electronic versions of vintage newspapers via touchscreen, experiencing the reading feel of the lead-type era. Themed wall panels connect key nodes in Chongqing''s press history—from the story of Baixiang Street''s "Newspaper Row" to the wartime years of Xinhua Daily in Chongqing. This micro-gallery hidden beside the train-through-building offers visitors a unique window into understanding Chongqing through the lens of journalism.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_liziba_monorail_sa_05';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '轨道穿楼主体建筑',
  name_en = 'Train-Through-Building Main Structure',
  body = '<p>The train-through-building main structure is a multi-use residential-commercial building on Liziba Zheng Street in Yuzhong District, built in the early 2000s, and also the station building for Liziba Station on Chongqing Metro Line 2. The 19-story building houses the metro platform and tracks on the 6th to 8th floors, with trains passing directly through the middle of the structure. The lower floors (1–5) contain shops, and the upper floors (9–19) house residential apartments. This unique "rail-residential coexistence" design is extremely rare both nationally and globally. Its secret lies in the independent load-bearing structure and vibration isolation system between the track level and residential floors—track beams are supported by dedicated columns completely separated from the residential floor slabs, so residents upstairs barely feel vibration or noise when trains pass through. The exterior is clad in light-colored tiles, with two square openings where trains emerge and re-enter serving as the most recognizable visual symbols. Each time a train roars through, the massive body emerging from and disappearing into the building is a textbook example of urban architecture and rail transit integration, making this building one of Chongqing''s most famous city cards.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_liziba_monorail_sa_06';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '朝天门广场与两江交汇',
  name_en = 'Chaotianmen Square and the Confluence of Two Rivers',
  body = '<p>nightly两江游船由此启航。来福士广场建筑群矗立于广场后方，如风帆拔地而起，与朝天门的历史厚重形成新旧对话。夜幕降临，两岸灯光璀璨倒映江面，是拍摄重庆夜景的绝佳机位。 Chaotianmen Square sits at the confluence of the Yangtze and Jialing rivers, and has been Chongqing''s water gateway and urban origin since ancient times. Standing at the front railing, visitors can see the jade-green Jialing River on the left and the muddy-yellow Yangtze on the right, forming a striking two-color waterline where the rivers meet. Chaotianmen was first built in the early Ming Dynasty and was the largest of the seventeen ancient city gates. Today, after multiple renovations, the square has become a core landmark for leisure and sightseeing. Below lies Chaotianmen Pier, where nightly river cruise boats depart. The Raffles City complex rises behind the square like a cluster of sails, creating a dialogue between old and new. At night, dazzling lights from both banks reflect on the water, making it one of the best spots to photograph Chongqing''s nightscape.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_raffles_city_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '购物中心中庭与山城花园',
  name_en = 'Shopping Mall Atrium and Mountain City Garden',
  body = '<p>The Raffles City shopping mall atrium draws inspiration from Chongqing''s mountainous terrain, creating a tiered, three-dimensional space that mimics the traditional stilt-house architecture built along hillsides, cleverly blending commercial space with the city''s topography. The atrium rises dozens of meters with skylights flooding natural light, and cascading greenery hangs from above to create an immersive rainforest-like atmosphere. The Mountain City Garden, located on the mall''s rooftop, is an open-air sky garden featuring over a hundred plant species native to Chongqing or adapted to subtropical climates. Winding paths connect multiple resting spots and viewing nodes overlooking the Jialing River and Chaotianmen Square—a peaceful urban oasis. The mall hosts international and local designer brands, and the atrium regularly features art exhibitions and seasonal installations, elevating the shopping experience into a cultural journey.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_raffles_city_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '水晶连廊（探索舱·观景台）',
  name_en = 'The Crystal (Exploration Deck · Observation Deck)',
  body = '<p>AR体验装置。日落时分，金色阳光洒满江面，是拍摄两江交汇与朝天门全景的最佳时机。 The Crystal is the most iconic architectural element of Raffles City—a approximately 300-meter-long crystal bridge spanning the tops of four 250-meter-tall towers, suspended like a crystal arc above the mountain city''s skyline. Designed by internationally acclaimed architect Moshe Safdie, it draws inspiration from the "sail" imagery of Chongqing''s millennia-old shipping culture. The Exploration Deck, located inside the Crystal, is the public observation experience area. Through floor-to-ceiling panoramic glass walls, visitors can enjoy 360-degree views of the Yangtze and Jialing rivers'' confluence, the rolling peaks of Nanshan in the distance, and Yuzhong Peninsula''s urban forest below. Interactive exhibits introduce Chongqing''s river geography and urban evolution, with high-definition telescopes and AR devices. At sunset, golden light floods the river—the best time to photograph the two-river confluence and Chaotianmen panorama.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_raffles_city_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '探索舱·云端乐园',
  name_en = 'Exploration Deck · Sky Wonderland',
  body = '<p>VR技术模拟乘船穿越两江峡谷的震撼体验；星空漫步区在天花板安装LED星空穹顶，营造漫步云端银河的梦幻氛围。最受欢迎的当属高空玻璃观景栈道，透明玻璃地板悬空250米，脚下便是朝天门广场与两江汇流，胆大的游客可体验凌空行走的极致刺激。乐园还设有主题文创商店和云端咖啡吧，供游客在高空享受悠闲下午茶。整个体验约需1.5至2小时，是来福士最热门的深度体验项目。 The Exploration Deck · Sky Wonderland is an upgraded immersive experience within the Crystal, combining technology interaction, art installations, and themed adventure on top of basic observation. The wonderland features multiple themed zones: the City Memory Zone uses holographic projections and touchscreens to showcase Chongqing''s millennia of evolution from ancient pier to modern metropolis; the River Exploration Zone uses VR to simulate the thrilling experience of boating through two-river gorges; the Star Walk Zone features an LED starry sky ceiling creating a dreamy atmosphere of walking among clouds and galaxies. The most popular attraction is the high-altitude glass observation walkway—a transparent glass floor suspended 250 meters above Chaotianmen Square and the river confluence, offering the ultimate thrill of walking on air. A themed merchandise shop and cloud-top café let visitors enjoy afternoon tea at altitude. The full experience takes about 1.5 to 2 hours, making it Raffles City''s most popular in-depth attraction.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_raffles_city_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '天龙桥',
  name_en = 'Tianlong Bridge (Heavenly Dragon Bridge)',
  body = '<p>Tianlong Bridge is the first natural stone arch bridge in Wulong''s Three Natural Bridges scenic area and the most imposing of the three. The bridge was formed from limestone deposited on an ancient seabed hundreds of millions of years ago, subsequently uplifted by tectonic movement and sculpted by water erosion and collapse. The arch stands approximately 235 meters high, with a bridge deck about 150 meters thick, 147 meters wide, and a span of about 34 meters—like a colossal stone rainbow spanning two cliff faces. The irregularly shaped arch opening allows sunlight to pour through from above, casting dappled light and shadow across the valley floor in a magnificent, dreamlike display. A winding stone-paved trail passes beneath the bridge, with ferns and vines clinging to the rock walls and moss-covered rubble scattered about, as if entering an ancient secret realm. The most famous feature is an eagle-shaped natural rock formation at the top of the arch and the "Thread Spring" trickling from beneath the vault. The hidden courier station from Zhang Yimou''s film "Curse of the Golden Flower" was filmed beneath Tianlong Bridge, and the replica structure remains as a must-visit photo spot. Walking beneath the bridge and looking up at the enormous vault overhead, one feels the overwhelming majesty of nature and the smallness of humanity.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_wulong_karst_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '仙女山国家公园-大草原站',
  name_en = 'Fairy Mountain National Park – Da Caoyuan Station (Great Meadow Station)',
  body = '<p>Da Caoyuan Station is the core stop of the Fairy Mountain National Park sightseeing train, located about 4 km after Mutizi Station at an elevation of approximately 2,000 meters. The moment visitors step off the train, the view opens dramatically—a vast alpine meadow stretching to the horizon, covering more than ten square kilometers, often called the "Switzerland of the East." The grassland undulates gently like a green velvet carpet—emerald green with scattered wildflowers in spring and summer (most commonly purple verbena, yellow coreopsis, and white wild strawberry blossoms), with cattle, sheep, and horses grazing peacefully in a pastoral idyll. In autumn, the meadow turns golden brown, contrasting vividly with the dark green Cryptomeria forest in the distance; in winter, thick snow transforms it into a rare southern snowfield, where the park operates a ski area and snow activities. After disembarking, visitors can choose from multiple experiences: horseback riding is the most classic, with local herdsmen leading horses along set routes for a leisurely "vast sky, boundless plain" experience; kite flying is also extremely popular, as the highland winds keep colorful kites dancing overhead; archery, grass sliding, and off-road go-karting are also available. A rest area, snack shop, and yurt-themed restaurant beside the station provide supplies and respite. Da Caoyuan Station is where visitors spend the most time—with most staying at least 2–3 hours to enjoy the abundant activities.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_wulong_karst_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '天官赐福',
  name_en = 'Tianguan Cifu (Heavenly Official''s Blessing)',
  body = '<p>Tianguan Cifu is a unique natural cliff-face feature beneath Tianlong Bridge in the Three Natural Bridges scenic area. On the inner wall of the northern arch of Tianlong Bridge, a pattern of stone veins—formed over hundreds of millions of years through water erosion and mineral staining—strikingly resembles the four Chinese characters "天官赐福" (Heavenly Official''s Blessing). The strokes appear vigorous and well-structured, as if an immortal had used a finger as a brush to write on the cliff face. This coincidence has circulated in folklore for generations; local people regard it as an auspicious mark bestowed by a heavenly official descending to earth. During New Year and major celebrations, nearby villagers come to burn incense and pray for favorable weather and household peace. The surrounding cliff also bears natural patterns resembling auspicious clouds, bats, and ruyi motifs, further reinforcing the auspicious symbolism of fortune, prosperity, longevity, and happiness. The scenic area has installed a viewing platform, information plaque, and soft lighting so visitors can appreciate this natural wonder under various conditions. Geologically, the pattern results from differential weathering of varying mineral compositions in the limestone and iron oxide staining—a natural formation that, due to its striking resemblance to Chinese characters, has become one of the most culturally significant geological wonders of the Wulong Karst.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_wulong_karst_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '青龙桥',
  name_en = 'Qinglong Bridge (Azure Dragon Bridge)',
  body = '<p>Qinglong Bridge is the second natural stone arch bridge in the Three Natural Bridges scenic area and the tallest of the three, with an arch height of approximately 281 meters, a deck thickness of about 168 meters, a width of about 124 meters, and a span of about 31 meters—ranking among the tallest natural stone arch bridges in the world. The bridge spans a near-vertical karst canyon, resembling a colossal stone archway standing between heaven and earth. The name comes from a beautiful natural phenomenon: at sunrise, sunlight slants through the arch opening, and the light refracts through mist and water vapor to form a blue-green beam crossing the canyon—like an azure dragon soaring through the bridge. A stream flows along the valley floor, with stalactites hanging from the rock walls in various forms—some like swords piercing the ground, others like lotus buds about to bloom. The arch ceiling has developed alcoves and natural stone eaves through weathering. During the rainy season, water cascades from these eaves like a bead curtain, with rainbows appearing in the sunlight—a dreamlike scene. A viewing platform beneath Qinglong Bridge offers one of the best vantage points for photographing the "soaring azure dragon" sunrise spectacle and classic panoramic views of the Three Natural Bridges.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_wulong_karst_sa_05';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '神鹰天坑',
  name_en = 'Shenying Tiankeng (Divine Eagle Doline)',
  body = '<p>Shenying Tiankeng is a large karst collapse doline situated between Tianlong Bridge and Qinglong Bridge in the Three Natural Bridges scenic area. The doline has an elliptical plan with a rim diameter of about 200–300 meters and a depth of approximately 195 meters, with a total volume of several million cubic meters—a world-class karst collapse feature. The doline is enclosed by nearly vertical limestone cliffs whose surfaces, through differential weathering, have formed numerous lifelike rock formations. The most striking is a protruding boulder on the eastern rim that, from certain angles, resembles a soaring eagle with head held high, wings spread, and piercing gaze overlooking the doline floor—giving the feature its name "Divine Eagle." The doline floor is relatively flat, covered with thick collapse deposits and subsequently grown dense vegetation, forming a relatively isolated "hanging garden" ecosystem. Wildflowers carpet sunlit areas while ferns thrive in shady corners, and birds occasionally circle above. Visitors descend along a cliff-hugging boardwalk, appreciating the doline''s grandeur and the Eagle Rock from different heights and angles. Standing at the bottom looking up, the surrounding walls form a natural shaft with the sky cut into an irregular ellipse where clouds drift overhead—an extraordinary sense of isolation from the world.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_wulong_karst_sa_06';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '黑龙桥',
  name_en = 'Heilong Bridge (Black Dragon Bridge)',
  body = '<p>Heilong Bridge is the third and final natural stone arch bridge in the Three Natural Bridges scenic area, with an arch height of approximately 223 meters, a deck thickness of about 137 meters, a width of about 193 meters, and a span of about 28 meters. Unlike Tianlong Bridge''s grandeur and Qinglong Bridge''s height, Heilong Bridge is renowned for its depth, darkness, and unpredictability. The long, curving arch opening admits little sunlight, leaving the interior perpetually dim with cool breezes and the sound of flowing water—walking through feels like traversing a black dragon''s belly, hence the name "Black Dragon." The most famous feature is the natural perforation in the arch ceiling through which sunlight enters, creating a bright spot on the dark wall that slowly moves over time like a searchlight scanning the cave—dubbed the "Shadow Clock." Multiple remarkable micro-karst formations exist beneath: a stalactite platform resembling Guanyin seated on a lotus, rock strata sections as clean-cut as by knife, and miniature stalagmite clusters formed by perennial dripping. Near the exit, a narrow passage called "Dragon Gate" has walls nearly touching, admitting only one person sideways—after squeezing through, the space suddenly opens into a hidden paradise. Summer temperatures beneath Heilong Bridge are only about 18°C, making it a natural cooling refuge and the most adventure-filled of the three bridges.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_wulong_karst_sa_07';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '龙泉洞',
  name_en = 'Longquan Cave (Dragon Spring Cave)',
  body = '<p>Longquan Cave is hidden within a limestone cliff face near Heilong Bridge in the Three Natural Bridges scenic area—one of the most mysterious cave features in the park. The entrance is concealed beneath a moss-covered cliff, where a clear mountain spring gushes from within, cascading along the rock face into a thin stream that drops to the valley floor. The perpetual flow and the low, dragon-like rumble of the water give it the name "Dragon Spring." The explored length extends several hundred meters, divided into front and rear chambers. The front chamber is spacious with a vault about 15 meters high, walls covered in diverse stalactites and stone curtains—some like inverted lotus flowers, others like terraced fields or hanging silk drapes—gleaming under lighting. The rear chamber is deeper and narrower, requiring visitors to stoop; the ceiling is dense with soda straw stalactites like a volley of arrows, while several stalagmites and columns rise from the floor. The tallest stalagmite, about 3 meters high, resembles a miniature pagoda, formed over tens of thousands of years of drip deposition. The cave maintains a constant temperature of about 16°C year-round—refreshingly cool in summer and misty in winter. Ancient marine fossils are visible on the cave walls, silently recounting the epic geological journey from ocean floor to mountain peak over hundreds of millions of years. Though smaller than Wulong''s Furong Cave, Longquan Cave''s exquisite delicacy and seamless integration with the Three Natural Bridges make it an unmissable hidden gem.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_wulong_karst_sa_08';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '龙水峡地缝',
  name_en = 'Longshuixia Difeng (Dragon Water Gorge Fissure)',
  body = '<p>Longshuixia Difeng is an important component of the Wulong Karst World Natural Heritage. It belongs to the same geological system as the Three Natural Bridges but presents a dramatically different landscape. The fissure extends about 5 km total with a developed tourist section of about 2 km—a deep gorge-type karst landform formed by the collapse of an underground river''s ceiling. At its narrowest, the gorge is only 1–2 meters wide, with near-vertical cliff walls 200–300 meters high. From the valley floor, the sky appears as a single thread—hence the names "Earth Fissure" and "Thread of Sky." A crystal-clear stream runs the length of the valley floor, jade-green in color, with water-polished boulders scattered throughout. Cliff-hugging boardwalks and suspended bridges wind through the gorge—visitors stroll along the streambank one moment and climb to mid-cliff aerial walkways the next, with only a sliver of sky overhead and rushing water below. Stalactites hang from the walls, thick with moss and ferns, as if entering a green tunnel toward the earth''s core. The microclimate is cool and humid, with air fragrant with plants and water mist; summer temperatures are about 10°C lower than outside. Multiple small waterfalls cascade from cliff crevices along the way, with mist and occasional rainbows. The most spectacular, Yinhe Waterfall, drops dozens of meters—the iconic feature of the fissure.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_wulong_karst_sa_09';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '银河飞瀑',
  name_en = 'Yinhe Waterfall (Milky Way Cascade)',
  body = '<p>Yinhe Waterfall is the largest and most awe-inspiring waterfall in the Longshuixia Difeng scenic area. Located at the mid-section of the gorge fissure, an abundant underground river source gushes from a natural crevice high on the cliff face, cascading down a near-vertical rock wall with a drop of several dozen meters. At full flow, the curtain spans 3–5 meters wide, roaring like thunder with mist filling the narrow gorge—an overwhelming spectacle. The great height and force shatter the water into countless fine droplets that refract sunlight into brilliant sparkles, like the Milky Way descending from heaven—hence the name "Milky Way Cascade." At its base, the waterfall collects into a deep emerald pool, clear to the bottom yet unfathomably deep, surrounded by mirror-smooth boulders polished by the current. From the viewing platform at the pool''s edge, mist washes over visitors—refreshingly cool in summer, while in winter it freezes into icicles and frost flowers adorning the cliffs, offering distinct beauty in every season. A natural alcove in the cliff behind the waterfall allows adventurous visitors to circle via a side boardwalk into the cave and look outward through the cascading curtain—a magical "Water Curtain Cave" experience. Yinhe Waterfall is the climactic section of the Longshuixia Difeng tour and one of the most memorable water features in the entire Wulong Karst tourist area.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_wulong_karst_sa_10';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '蛟龙寒窟',
  name_en = 'Jiaolong Hangu (Flood Dragon Cold Cave)',
  body = '<p>Jiaolong Hangu is located beneath a cliff deep within the Longshuixia Difeng scenic area—a natural large stone cavern formed by the combined action of karst dissolution and rock layer collapse. The entrance is low and concealed, half-hidden by dense ferns and moss, requiring visitors to duck to enter. The interior space covers several dozen square meters with a vault about 3–5 meters high. The walls are covered with grooves and dissolution pits formed by perennial water erosion, their surfaces wet and smooth, gleaming with a cold sheen under lighting. The cavern''s most notable feature is its exceptionally low temperature—about 12–14°C year-round. Even in midsummer, the chill upon entering is biting and bone-penetrating, with a temperature difference of more than 15°C from outside. A shallow cold pool occupies the cavern floor, crystal-clear and icy, inhabited by tiny blind fish and transparent shrimp—cave-dwelling species evolved for perpetual darkness, their bodies pale or colorless. Behind the pool, a narrow underground river channel extends deeper into the earth, its water echoing faintly, with even searchlights unable to reach the end—shrouding the cavern in mystery. Local folklore holds that a flood dragon once lurked here, its dragon breath becoming the perpetual cold mist, hence the name "Flood Dragon Cold Cave." Though modest in size, the extreme chill and mysterious underground ecosystem make this one of the most memorable exploration stops in the Longshuixia Difeng tour.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_wulong_karst_sa_11';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '仙女山国家公园-木梯子站',
  name_en = 'Fairy Mountain National Park – Mutizi Station',
  body = '<p>Mutizi Station is the starting station of the sightseeing train within Fairy Mountain National Park, located near the main park road entrance at an elevation of about 1,900 meters—the first stop for visitors entering the core scenic area. The name "Mutizi" (Wooden Ladder) originates from local history: a steep mountain path once paved with wooden stairs here was the main route for early mountain dwellers to gather herbs and graze livestock. After the road was built, the stairs fell into disuse, but the name endured. The station building features wooden construction with grey tiles in Ba-Yu mountain vernacular style, harmonizing with the surrounding pine forest and alpine meadows. The plaza in front includes a large visitor distribution area, ticket windows, a resting corridor, and park maps. After purchasing tickets, visitors board a vintage sightseeing train that runs along a circular railway through the park. The 12-kilometer route passes through dense Cryptomeria and cypress forests and alpine meadows with seasonal variation: lush green grass and wildflowers in spring and summer, layered autumn colors, and a silvery snowscape in winter resembling northern landscapes. Mutizi Station also houses a transfer center and ecological parking lot where self-driving visitors park before taking the train into the core scenic area. An open lawn beside the station is equipped with telescopes for viewing Fairy Mountain''s main peak and the rolling Wuling range—an ideal spot for warm-up photos before departure.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_wulong_karst_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '层空中公共连廊',
  name_en = 'th-Floor Sky Corridor',
  body = '<p>Built in 1996, this 24-floor residential block has no elevator. The 10th-floor corridor links the three towers of the complex, offering unobstructed views of the Yangtze, the cable car, the Raffles City skyline and the Yangtze River Bridge—an iconic filming and viral-photography location famous for Chongqing''s "8D magic."</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_baixiangju_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '层解放东路出口（终点）',
  name_en = 'th-Floor Jiefang East Road Exit (Ending Point)',
  body = '<p>This 15th-floor exit connects Baixiangju to Jiefang East Road and the Luohan Temple area via a 30-step descent. The platform offers a striking 3D-traffic view of Jiefang East Road, Minzu Road, Cangbai Road, the cable car and double-decker buses, marking the official end of the Baixiangju vertical tour.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_baixiangju_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '层临江入口（起点）',
  name_en = 'Ground-Floor Riverside Entrance (Starting Point)',
  body = '<p>The riverside entrance on the ground floor of Baixiangju is the starting point of the vertical tour. It features two 2-meter stone elephants, a 1990s residential block hugging the Yangtze and the famous air-raid-shelter-turned-café that has become a viral photo spot for the Chongqing skyline and cable car.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_baixiangju_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '长江索道同框观景窗',
  name_en = 'Cable-Car Frame Window',
  body = '<p>This framed cable-car shot, captured from the 10th-floor corridor''s east end with a 2–3x telephoto lens, places the Yangtze Cable Car and Baixiangju''s 24-story walk-up in the same frame. The result—an "8D" composition of building, cable car and river—has become a must-shoot for photographers worldwide.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_baixiangju_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '磁器长歌体验馆',
  name_en = '"Ciqi Changge" Immersive Experience Hall',
  body = '<p>Opened in May 2023, Ciqi Changge is Ciqikou''s first large-scale immersive night-experience hall. Across five acts—Ancient Wharf, Old Street, Porcelain Kiln, Guild Hall, Wartime Capital—it uses AR, holograms, live performance and interactive lighting to compress 1,000 years of local history into a 60-minute walking show.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_ciqikou_old_town_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '黄桷坪牌坊',
  name_en = 'Huangjueping Memorial Arch',
  body = '<p>Rebuilt in 2010 in classic Ming style, this 12-meter stone archway is the official entrance to Ciqikou Ancient Town. Flanked by two 100-year-old banyan trees and the "Ciqikou" name tablet, it marks the starting point of both the main street and the riverside tour routes.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_ciqikou_old_town_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '钟家院',
  name_en = 'Zhong Family Mansion',
  body = '<p>Built in the Xianfeng era (1851–1861), the 1,500 m² Zhong Mansion is a three-bay Qing residence with a front shop and a back living area. Converted into the Bayu Folk-House Museum in 1998, it displays wedding customs, carved beds, ancestral tablets and other late-imperial artifacts of Bayu culture.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_ciqikou_old_town_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '宝善宫',
  name_en = 'Baoshan Palace',
  body = '<p>Built in 1886 as a Jiangxi merchant guild hall, Baoshan Palace is the best-preserved of Ciqikou''s "Nine Palaces and Eighteen Temples." Refurbished in 2010, its teahouse hosts Sichuan opera seating performances daily, with bamboo chairs and 5-CNY covered-bowl tea—a perfect taste of old Chongqing.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_ciqikou_old_town_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '鑫记杂货铺',
  name_en = 'Xin''s Grocery',
  body = '<p>Founded in 1894, Xin''s is a fourth-generation grocery and the only shop still using the traditional "front-shop-back-workshop" layout on Ciqikou''s main street. It sells malt sugar, sesame candy, hand-made soy sauce, Sichuan pepper broad-bean paste and dozens of other old Chongqing snacks—a living window into late-imperial market culture.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_ciqikou_old_town_sa_05';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '聚森茂酱园旧址',
  name_en = 'Jusenmao Sauce Garden Site',
  body = '<p>Founded in 1911, Jusenmao was once the largest sauce maker in Ciqikou, producing 500,000 jin of soy sauce, vinegar, bean paste and pickles a year. Partially demolished in 2003, its front shop and sun-curing yard were rebuilt in 2010 as a museum of traditional sauce culture, with 60+ vats on display.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_ciqikou_old_town_sa_06';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '磁横街',
  name_en = 'Ciheng Street',
  body = '<p>Built along the Jialing River cliff, the 200-meter "half-side street" is Ciqikou''s most authentic riverside market. With stilted houses, stone steps, dock-worker statues and ancient banyans, it preserves the late-Qing water-and-land transport hub that made Ciqikou a leading commercial port in eastern Sichuan.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_ciqikou_old_town_sa_07';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '宝轮寺',
  name_en = 'Baolun Temple',
  body = '<p>Founded in 1008 during the Tang dynasty, Baolun Temple is the origin of the "White Rock" name for Ciqikou. Rebuilt in the Kangxi era and bestowed the imperial name "Baolun Chan Temple" by Emperor Qianlong, it preserves a Kangxi plaque, Song stone Buddhas and Ming gilt-bronze statues—the three treasures of the temple.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_ciqikou_old_town_sa_08';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '迎龙门码头',
  name_en = 'Yinglongmen Wharf',
  body = '<p>Dating back to the Ming dynasty, Yinglongmen Wharf was one of the four major Jialing River ports in the late-Qing era, handling 300,000 tons of cargo annually. Restored in 2010 with its stone steps, mooring stones and river pavilion, it now hosts folk performers and is the boarding point for Jialing River cruise boats.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_ciqikou_old_town_sa_09';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '九石缸河滩',
  name_en = 'Nine-Stone-Cap Riverside',
  body = '<p>The viral "Little Kenting" beach, named after nine Qing-era stone vats once used to store drinking water for porcelain-export boats. Six of the nine vats survive today, lining a sandy Jialing River bank popular from May to October for wading, sunset views and winter misty mornings.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_ciqikou_old_town_sa_10';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '名字：观音桥步行街广场',
  name_en = 'Guanyinqiao Pedestrian Street Plaza',
  body = '<p>Covering 58,000 sqm, the plaza was created during the 2003 redevelopment and now welcomes 150 million visitors a year. It links 10+ shopping malls, two metro lines and the central "Jinjie" underground street.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_guanyinqiao_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '名字：茂业天地"裸眼 3D"大屏',
  name_en = 'Maoye Tiandi Naked-Eye 3D Screen',
  body = '<p>D"大屏位于江北区观音桥步行街东端、茂业天地（江北店）外立面，于 2021 年 1 月点亮，是重庆首块商业级户外裸眼 3D 巨幕。屏幕总面积约 700 平方米，采用 P3 高清 LED 曲面显示技术，分辨率近 4K，曲面转角设计结合周边建筑形态，使播放内容产生强烈的"破屏而出"立体视觉。该大屏长期播放"赛博重庆"主题短片、洪崖洞立体动画、虚拟机器人、海洋生物等 3D 内容，是观音桥商圈最具科技感与人气的"打卡屏"，与成都春熙路太古里裸眼 3D 大屏、纽约时代广场大屏并称"全球三大裸眼 3D 屏"。2022 年起带动重庆"赛博朋克"夜游 IP 出圈。 A 700 sqm curved P3 LED screen on Maoye Tiandi''s façade, lit in January 2021, displaying "Cyber Chongqing" 3D animations. It is one of the most photographed night attractions in the CBD.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_guanyinqiao_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '名字：观音桥雕塑（城市标志）',
  name_en = 'Guanyinqiao Sculpture (City Landmark)',
  body = '<p>LED 灯带，夜间会随商圈主题切换不同颜色（如春节红、樱花粉、圣诞金）。整座雕塑既呼应了"观音桥"地名由来——清嘉庆年间此处建有观音庙与跨街石桥，又以抽象现代手法象征江北区"开放、包容"的城市精神，是游客到访观音桥必合影的城市地标。 The 16.8 m stainless-steel sculpture with its "Guanyin praying" figure and Chongqing landscape base was unveiled in 2003, refurbished in 2018 and has become the central photo landmark of the CBD.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_guanyinqiao_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '名字：北城天街',
  name_en = 'Beicheng Tianjie (North City Mall)',
  body = '<p>A 区、B 区、C 区（北城天街 PLUS 星光 68）与 X 区四个商业体组成。A 区定位中高端零售与国际名品；B 区主打潮流时尚与餐饮；C 区星光 68 引入 LV、Gucci、Tiffany 等一线奢侈品牌；X 区聚焦夜经济与娱乐体验。商场内常设艺术展陈空间与西南地区最大 Apple Store，是重庆"潮人聚集地"和"潮流风向标"。 A 380,000 sqm shopping complex opened by Longfor in 2003, comprising Blocks A, B, C (Starlight 68) and X. It houses luxury brands, fashion, dining and entertainment, and is the CBD''s flagship mall.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_guanyinqiao_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '名字：观音桥九街（不夜九街 - 终点）',
  name_en = 'Guanyinqiao Jiugie (Sleepless Jiugie - Terminal)',
  body = '<p>Live House、深夜食堂、潮流买手店与 24 小时不打烊的烧烤/小龙虾店——"九街烤鱼""九街大排档"已成重庆夜宵文化代表。九街夜场从 20:00 持续至次日凌晨 4:00，是"赛博重庆"夜游路线与"不夜城"体验不可错过的终点节点。 A 1.2 km nightlife zone with 200+ bars, live houses and 24 h eateries, opened as a pilot "night-economy district" in 2017. Open from 20:00 to 04:00, it is the after-dark terminal of the route.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_guanyinqiao_sa_05';

