UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '大门广场（起点）',
  name_en = 'Main Entrance Plaza (Starting Point)',
  body = '<p>The semi-circular entrance plaza greets visitors with a giant panda flower bed, a golden "Chongqing Zoo" sign, palm and ginkgo trees, and bronze animal statues. It also houses the visitor center, ticket office, souvenir shop and the official park map—making it the natural starting point for any visit.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_zoo_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '熊猫馆',
  name_en = 'Panda Hall',
  body = '<p>Built in the 1960s and modernized in the 2010s, Panda Hall is a multi-zone complex with indoor halls, outdoor playgrounds, a maternity ward and a kindergarten. Home to 10+ giant pandas, it is one of the largest breeding bases in western China and a flagship for panda research, conservation and education.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_zoo_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '金鱼馆',
  name_en = 'Goldfish Hall',
  body = '<p>Built in the 1990s and refurbished in 2018, Goldfish Hall is a southwest-China landmark for goldfish appreciation. With four themed zones and ~60 varieties (dragon-eye, fantail, oranda, ranchu, celestial-eye, pearl-scale and more), it is a favorite for family visits and a regular venue for the National Goldfish Competition.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_zoo_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '两栖爬行动物馆',
  name_en = 'Amphibian and Reptile Hall',
  body = '<p>Opened in 2005, the Amphibian and Reptile Hall is the largest herpetarium in southwest China. With two floors and habitats mimicking rainforest, marsh, rocky desert and river valley, it houses 60+ species and 300+ individuals, plus a "night-creature" interactive zone popular with school groups.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_zoo_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '鸟类区',
  name_en = 'Bird Area',
  body = '<p>The 15,000 m² Bird Area is the largest and most diverse in the zoo, comprising six themed zones and home to nearly 100 species. Highlights include red-crowned cranes, mandarin ducks, golden pheasants, peafowl, hornbills, macaws, flamingos and the rare Chinese crested tern, with seasonal wild birds joining the resident flocks in spring and autumn.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_zoo_sa_05';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '大门',
  name_en = 'Main Gate (North Gate)',
  body = '<p>The Main Gate sits at the foot of Jinfo Mountain''s north slope near Tianxing Town and serves as the first stop for most visitors. The entrance complex combines a large parking lot, visitor center, ticket windows and self-service kiosks where combined tickets for admission, cableway and shuttle can be purchased. An eco-shuttle bus ride of about 20 minutes reaches the cableway lower station, passing lower-zone sights such as Bitan Valley. The visitor center offers panoramic maps, rain-poncho rental and luggage storage, and doubles as the registration point for winter ski equipment. Outside the gate, Tianxing Town provides dining, lodging and specialty shops—a common base for two-day "valley-to-summit" itineraries.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_jinfo_mountain_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '碧潭幽谷',
  name_en = 'Bitan Valley (Green Pool Secluded Gorge)',
  body = '<p>Located at 700–1,000 m elevation on Jinfo Mountain''s north slope, Bitan Valley is the key lower-zone landscape along the route from the main gate to the cableway lower station. The roughly 3 km gorge winds up along a mountain stream between steep, densely forested cliffs that shelter rare species such as yew and dove tree. Over a dozen deep pools dot the valley—the largest, "Bitan" (Emerald Pool), is jade-green and translucent, traditionally said to be where ancient monks washed their alms bowls. Wooden boardwalks and stone paths pass waterfalls, cascades and moss-covered walls; summer temperatures run 5–8 °C cooler than the base, making this a classic hot-season hiking route. The full walk takes about 1.5–2 hours.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_jinfo_mountain_sa_08';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '索道下站',
  name_en = 'Cableway Lower Station (North Slope)',
  body = '<p>The West Gate Cableway Lower Station sits at the foot of Jinfo Mountain''s west slope at about 700 m—the starting point of the western passenger cableway. At roughly 2.4 km long with a 1.3 km elevation gain, the 15-minute ride is the longer and more scenically varied of Jinfo Mountain''s two cableways. Cabins climb along a ridge, offering aerial views of primeval forest, stream-fed waterfalls and distant cloud seas; autumn foliage and winter rime-and-ice scenes are spectacular. The lower station has a waiting hall, ticket windows and a parking lot, plus an adjoining west-slope visitor center and dining facilities. The western route generally has fewer visitors and shorter queues than the north slope, ideal for self-drivers arriving via the western G65 expressway. An outside platform frames the western face of the main summit ridge.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_jinfo_mountain_sa_06';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '牵牛坪天街',
  name_en = 'Qianniuping Sky Street',
  body = '<p>Qianniuping Sky Street lies at the exit of the north-slope cableway upper station at about 2,000 m, named after the Qianniuping meadow. It is the hub of Jinfo Mountain''s summit zone, with restaurants, specialty shops, a convenience store, a café and viewing terraces offering local delicacies such as square-bamboo shoots, Jinshan cured meat and alpine potatoes. A large route map at the plaza helps visitors choose directions: east to Golden Turtle and Cloud Walkway, west to Medicine Pool Dam and Ancient Buddha Cave, north to Arrow Bamboo Forest and Azalea Prince. In winter the street becomes the ski-service center with equipment rental and access to the ski slope. Lodging here makes summit sunrise and stargazing possible.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_jinfo_mountain_sa_10';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '箭竹林海',
  name_en = 'Arrow Bamboo Forest Sea',
  body = '<p>The Arrow Bamboo Forest Sea covers over 10 km² at 1,900–2,100 m on Jinfo Mountain''s summit, dominated by West-China arrow bamboo (Fargesia) standing 2–4 m tall in dense, sun-dimming stands. As a core zone of the national nature reserve, it shelters rare species such as musk deer, golden pheasant and white-crowned fork-tail, and lies along the southern potential corridor of the giant panda''s historical range. Wooden boardwalks thread through the groves—rustling leaves and cool breezes in summer, golden-tipped bamboo contrasting with autumn colors. Arrow bamboo flowers once every 60–120 years, after which entire stands die off and naturally regenerate, a key research subject for the mountain''s ecologists. An eco-education signboard and rest pavilion mark the entrance.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_jinfo_mountain_sa_11';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '金龟朝阳',
  name_en = 'Golden Turtle Facing the Sun',
  body = '<p>Golden Turtle Facing the Sun perches on the eastern cliff edge of Qianniuping at about 2,100 m and is one of Jinfo Mountain''s most recognizable rock formations. Shaped from Cambrian limestone over hundreds of millions of years of weathering and dissolution, the roughly 10 m long, 5 m high boulder resembles—when viewed from the east—a giant stone turtle lifting its head toward the sun, its shell, head and limbs clearly defined. Facing open valleys to the east, it is the mountain''s premier sunrise spot: dawn clouds churn, the sun crests the ridge, and golden light floods the turtle''s back. A wooden viewing platform with safety rails and an interpretive sign stands here; connecting trails lead to the Cloud Walkway and cliff-hugging plank road, making it the key node of the summit''s eastern route.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_jinfo_mountain_sa_12';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '云端步道',
  name_en = 'Cloud Walkway',
  body = '<p>The Cloud Walkway runs along the cliff face between Qianniuping and Golden Turtle at 2,000–2,100 m, stretching about 1.5 km—the most iconic aerial route on Jinfo Mountain''s eastern summit. Carved along a karst escarpment with sections of cantilevered steel, it places a rock wall on one side and a plunging valley on the other; when mist swirls in, walking it feels like treading on clouds—hence the name. Three projecting viewing platforms offer views of the Nanchuan mountain ranges and the lower-zone gorges, and are prime spots for the mountain''s "Buddha''s halo" and sea of clouds. The full route has safety rails and anti-slip surfacing; it may close in rain, and those with acrophobia should proceed with caution. A safety signboard and rest pavilion mark the entrance.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_jinfo_mountain_sa_13';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '燕子洞和灵观洞',
  name_en = 'Swallow Cave and Lingguan Cave',
  body = '<p>Swallow Cave and Lingguan Cave lie about 200 m apart on the west side of Qianniuping and form key parts of Jinfo Mountain''s karst-cave system. Swallow Cave has a roughly 15 m wide, 8 m high entrance opening into a spacious chamber where thousands of rock swallows nest year-round; in spring and summer they dart in and out like dark arrows—hence the name. Inside, an underground stream and stalagmites, curtains and flowstone decorate the chamber. Lingguan Cave is named for a Daoist Lingguan statue once placed at its mouth; its interior features stalactites, columns and cave flowers, with some walls bearing natural "Buddha" silhouettes where monks and Daoist priests once practiced. Both caves are lit and equipped with boardwalks; the interior temperature holds at 12–15 °C, so an extra layer is advisable in summer. Visiting both takes about 40–60 minutes.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_jinfo_mountain_sa_14';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '杜鹃王子',
  name_en = 'Azalea Prince',
  body = '<p>The "Azalea Prince" stands at the edge of the Arrow Bamboo Forest at about 2,050 m—an estimated 1,000-year-old wild Rhododendron rex, roughly 12 m tall, 40 cm in trunk diameter and nearly 8 m across the crown, making it the largest ancient wild rhododendron discovered on Jinfo Mountain. The mountain is a diversity center for Chinese rhododendrons, hosting over 40 species including more than 10 endemics. Each April–May the Prince bursts into bloom, its 10 cm-wide flowers ranging from pink to deep crimson, layered against a backdrop of bamboo, moss and multicolored forests—the most photographed spot of Jinfo Mountain''s spring season and a key site for botanical education. A boardwalk, viewing platform and interpretive sign stand beside the tree.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_jinfo_mountain_sa_15';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '药池坝',
  name_en = 'Yaochiba (Medicine Pool Dam)',
  body = '<p>Yaochiba sits southwest of Qianniuping at about 2,000 m—a roughly 30,000 m² alpine meadow and wetland complex. The flat, grassy expanse is dotted with dozens of natural mineral springs and pools; Jinfo Mountain monks once drew water here to brew herbal remedies, giving the place its name ("Medicine Pool"). Surrounded by arrow bamboo and rhododendron shrub, with the Jinfo summit ridge and karst pinnacles on the horizon, the meadow turns golden in autumn against layered forests—one of the mountain''s signature fall scenes. Boardwalks, rest pavilions and viewing platforms are provided, and the dam is a popular camping and stargazing spot. Westward trails lead to Ancient Buddha Cave and Jinfo Temple; southward to the Ecological Stone Forest.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_jinfo_mountain_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '古佛洞',
  name_en = 'Gufo Cave (Ancient Buddha Cave)',
  body = '<p>Gufo Cave lies west of Yaochiba at about 2,000 m and is the largest explored karst cave on Jinfo Mountain, with a total passage length of about 3 km and a developed tour route of roughly 1.2 km. Natural stone Buddha carvings at the entrance—believed to have been chiseled by monks in the Ming–Qing era from existing rock formations—gave the cave its name ("Ancient Buddha"). The interior is vast: the largest chamber rises about 30 m high and exceeds 5,000 m² in area, filled with stalagmites, stalactites, columns, curtains and cave flowers. The "Sea-Calming Pillar," a 15 m-tall, 1 m-diameter column, is the cave''s signature feature. Warm-yellow lighting enhances the Buddhist atmosphere, with several stone Buddha figures and sutra inscriptions along the route. The cave holds at 11–14 °C year-round with high humidity—wear non-slip footwear. The full walk takes 50–70 minutes.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_jinfo_mountain_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '金佛顶',
  name_en = 'Jinfo Summit (Jinfo Peak)',
  body = '<p>At about 2,238 m, Jinfo Summit is the highest point and spiritual symbol of Jinfo Mountain. The mountain takes its name from the main ridge''s resemblance to a reclining Buddha when seen from a distance, and the summit occupies the "head" position. From the top, visitors can survey 360° of the Dalou range; on clear days the Guizhou Dalou main ridge and Nanchuan city are visible. Nearby stands Jinfo Temple (Fengzui Temple), the mountain''s Buddhist heart—originally founded in the Song dynasty with later reconstructions, housing statues of Shakyamuni and Guanyin. The summit viewing platform with safety rails is the premier spot for sunrise, sea of clouds, "Buddha''s halo" and stargazing. In winter, snow can accumulate to tens of centimeters, creating a rare southern snow-field scene. The walk from Qianniuping Sky Street takes 40–50 minutes, partly on stone steps.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_jinfo_mountain_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '生态石林',
  name_en = 'Ecological Stone Forest',
  body = '<p>Covering about 2 km² south of Yaochiba at roughly 2,000 m, the Ecological Stone Forest is a key element of Jinfo Mountain''s karst landscape. Unlike the bare stone teeth of Yunnan''s Shilin, Jinfo''s pinnacles and stone buds are cloaked in moss, ferns, shrubs and trees—stone and forest merged into one, earning the name "living stone forest." The pinnacles, 3–8 m tall, take myriad forms—swords pointing skyward, beasts crouching among trees—interspersed with arrow bamboo, rhododendron and rare square bamboo, creating a unique "forest-on-stone" micro-ecosystem. In 2014 Jinfo Mountain was inscribed as part of the "South China Karst" Phase II World Natural Heritage, with the Ecological Stone Forest as a core heritage element. Boardwalks and interpretive signs guide visitors through a 30–40 minute walk—the best outdoor classroom for the mountain''s karst geology and biodiversity.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_jinfo_mountain_sa_05';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '西门游客中心',
  name_en = 'West Gate Visitor Center',
  body = '<p>The West Gate Visitor Center stands at the foot of the west slope beside the West Gate Cableway Lower Station, serving as the main entrance and service hub for the western route. The building blends modern functionality with mountain vernacular style, housing a large ticketing hall, self-service kiosks, an information desk, luggage storage, rain-poncho rental and a first-aid point, where visitors can purchase admission, cableway and shuttle combo tickets. Outside are a large parking lot, restrooms, dining outlets and specialty shops selling square-bamboo shoots, Nanchuan rice and dried local produce. Inside, a geology-and-biodiversity exhibit uses panels and specimens to introduce Jinfo Mountain''s World Natural Heritage karst geology, rare flora and fauna and rhododendron resources—an ideal "knowledge stop" before heading uphill. The walk from the center to the cableway lower station is about 3 minutes.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_jinfo_mountain_sa_07';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '北站（渝中区新华路站）',
  name_en = 'North Station (Xinhua Road Station, Yuzhong District)',
  body = '<p>The North Station of the Yangtze River Cableway is located near the intersection of Xinhua Road and Cangbai Road in the Xiaoshizi commercial area of Yuzhong District—the Yuzhong starting station and the preferred departure point for most visitors. The station building is a multi-story cableway complex with a light grey exterior and a prominent red "Yangtze River Cableway" sign that has become one of the iconic elements of the Yuzhong Peninsula skyline. The ground floor houses the ticket hall and waiting area with self-service machines and staffed windows. During peak season, queues can reach one to two hours—advance booking via the official mini-program is recommended. After purchasing tickets, visitors take an elevator to the high-level platform, a semi-open structure enclosed on three sides and open toward the river. A large floor-to-ceiling glass window lets waiting visitors overlook the dense urban fabric of the Yuzhong Peninsula and the rolling mountains of the south bank. The station''s greatest advantage is that departing cabins ascend from among the Yuzhong Peninsula''s high-rises, cross over the layered city roofline, and suddenly span the Yangtze—the visual transition from "city to river" is spectacular, making it the best starting point for panoramic photos of the peninsula and Yangtze skyline. A cableway history exhibition area beside the station displays archival construction photos and engineering documentation.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_yangtze_cableway_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '索道轿厢',
  name_en = 'Cableway Cabin',
  body = '<p>landmarks，夜晚乘坐更能欣赏渝中半岛灯火璀璨的夜景，是重庆最具代表性的城市体验项目之一。 The Yangtze River Cableway cabin is the core vehicle of the entire cableway experience, suspended on a carrying cable strung high above the Yangtze and hauled by a traction machine between North and South Stations. The cableway was completed and opened in 1987, with a total length of approximately 1,166 meters, a maximum height of about 60 meters above ground, and a one-way journey of about 4–5 minutes. The cabin features a bright yellow exterior, about 6.5 meters long, 1.5 meters wide, and 2 meters high, accommodating about 20–25 standing passengers. Large tempered glass windows on all four sides provide expansive views—the river surface, urban architecture on both banks, and rolling mountains are all clearly visible from front, sides, and below. The ride is unforgettable: the cabin departs slowly from the North Station platform, gradually accelerates, rises among dense city high-rises, and after crossing the north bank levee, the ground below suddenly becomes the open river—the mighty Yangtze flowing eastward, boats shuttling back and forth, with Chaotianmen Raffles City and Dongshuimen Bridge in the distance. At mid-river, the cabin sways gently with dozens of meters of rushing water below—thrilling and magnificent. On clear days, the Nanshan mountain peaks are visible in the distance; on foggy days, the cabin traverses through clouds like riding the mist. A voice guide inside introduces landmarks along the way. Night rides offer the dazzling illuminated skyline of the Yuzhong Peninsula—one of Chongqing''s most iconic urban experiences.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_yangtze_cableway_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '南站（南岸区龙门浩站）',
  name_en = 'South Station (Longmenhao Station, Nan''an District)',
  body = '<p>CBD 在眼前一字排开，是拍摄渝中半岛经典天际线的最佳位置之一，尤其日落和夜景时分景色最为壮丽。从南站出发乘坐索道向北站方向行驶时，轿厢从南岸高地向江面下降，视野从俯瞰全城逐渐过渡到平视江面和仰视渝中半岛楼群，与从北站出发的上升视角形成互补。南站出站后步行5分钟即可到达龙门浩老街，10分钟可达东水门大桥步道，是串联索道体验与南岸滨江游览的理想节点。 The South Station of the Yangtze River Cableway is located in the Longmenhao area of Nan''an District, on a riverside highland along the south bank of the Yangtze—the cableway''s southern terminal and the departure station for those boarding from the Nan''an side. Unlike the bustling Xiaoshizi commercial district where the North Station sits, the South Station''s surroundings are more leisurely and artistic—adjacent to the recently restored Longmenhao Old Street historic district, where blue-brick, dark-tile WWII-era buildings cascade up the hillside, dotted with cafés, teahouses, and creative boutiques. The station building is more compact than the North Station, with ticket windows, a waiting area, and a small observation platform. The platform level faces north toward the river, where floor-to-ceiling glass windows offer an unobstructed panoramic view of the entire Yuzhong Peninsula: the Chaotianmen Raffles City twin towers, Hongyadong complex, Qiansimen Bridge, and Jiangbeizui CBD arrayed before you—one of the best positions for photographing the classic Yuzhong Peninsula skyline, especially stunning at sunset and after dark. Riding from the South Station toward the North, the cabin descends from the south bank highland toward the river, with the view transitioning from a panoramic overlook to eye-level with the river surface and then looking up at the Yuzhong Peninsula towers—a perspective complementary to the ascending view from the North Station. A 5-minute walk from the station reaches Longmenhao Old Street, and 10 minutes reaches the Dongshuimen Bridge walkway—an ideal node linking the cableway experience with south bank riverside touring.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_yangtze_cableway_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '名字：鹅岭二厂文创公园大门',
  name_en = 'Eling Factory II Main Gate',
  body = '<p>T²"标识墙、复古路灯与立体绿植 LOGO 墙，形成"印钞厂记忆+工业再生"双重气质的迎宾空间。门口左侧巨幅"TESTBED 2"立体字与鹅岭地形图合影墙，是首次到访游客的必拍机位。 The main gate preserves the original 1930s sawtooth-roofed brick and steel-window structure of the Central Bank Printing Works, updated in 2014 with a "TESTBED 2" typographic wall and retro street lamps. It is the signature photo stop for first-time visitors.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_eling_2nd_factory_sa_01';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '名字：二厂记忆博物馆',
  name_en = 'Factory II Memory Museum',
  body = '<p>Housed in the original 8-metre-high brick hall of Building 5, the museum exhibits intaglio printing presses, numbering machines and engraved plates from the 1930s Central Bank Printing Works, plus a section on Chongqing''s wartime industrial history. Free admission.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_eling_2nd_factory_sa_07';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '名字：民国中央银行印钞厂旧址（9 号楼）',
  name_en = 'Former Central Bank Printing Works (Building 9)',
  body = '<p>Built in 1937 to print wartime currency, Building 9 is a three-storey 5,200 sqm brick building in "工" shape, designated a Chongqing Municipal Cultural Relic in 2013. Today the ground floor houses a café and design store; upper floors host artists-in-residence and photography studios.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_eling_2nd_factory_sa_08';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '名字：Test Design 街巷',
  name_en = 'Test Design Alley',
  body = '<p>Test Design 街巷位于园区中段、东侧连通大门与中心下沉广场的主动线，是二厂文创公园"设计力"主题业态的集中呈现。街巷两侧由原印钞厂仓库与连廊改造而来，红砖立面配黑色钢结构与落地玻璃，分布着十余家原创设计师店铺：从"ANNAKIKI""密扇 MUKZIN"等独立服装，到"本来设计""明暗"等原创家居，再到"梵誓 Fanci"等设计师首饰品牌。街巷中段设有一面"重庆森林"主题涂鸦墙与可更换的潮流海报墙，是园区客流量最大、网红打卡与设计师品牌共生的核心街巷。 Lined with red-brick warehouses converted into designer boutiques for fashion, homeware and jewelry, Test Design Alley is the park''s busiest retail street. A "Chongqing Forest" graffiti wall sits mid-alley.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_eling_2nd_factory_sa_09';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '名字：Test Joy 街巷',
  name_en = 'Test Joy Alley',
  body = '<p>Test Joy 街巷位于园区中部偏北、紧邻 9 号楼印钞厂旧址西侧，是二厂"快乐消费"主题业态的集中地。街巷由原印钞厂材料仓库改造而成，层高 5—7 米，钢筋外露、桁架完整，常态引入沉浸式剧本杀、密室逃脱、Live House 与二次元主题店；餐饮端则聚集了"埠口精酿""四村老火锅""椒房·新川菜"等重庆本地与异国料理品牌，并设有"鹅岭市集"周末手作市集区。Test Joy 街巷与 Test Design 街巷通过下沉广场相连，构成园区"东设计、西娱乐"的消费动线。 A 5–7 metre-high converted warehouse alley for immersive escape rooms, live houses and themed restaurants, Test Joy is the park''s "east design, west entertainment" companion to Test Design.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_eling_2nd_factory_sa_10';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '名字：爱情天台（CITY-RADIO 电台墙）',
  name_en = 'Love Rooftop (CITY-RADIO Wall)',
  body = '<p>CITY-RADIO 城市电台"主题涂鸦墙一举走红。电台墙以鹅岭山顶的"虚拟电台"为概念，墙面上绘有频率刻度盘、麦克风、电话听筒等元素，并设有可写明信片投递的"鹅岭邮筒"，是游客最钟爱的合影背景。傍晚时分天台可远眺渝中半岛与江北嘴夜景，是兼具人气与城市视野的浪漫点。 Filmed in the 2016 movie "I Belonged to You," the rooftop''s "CITY-RADIO" mural has become a must-photograph spot. The wall features a virtual radio dial, microphone and a working mailbox.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_eling_2nd_factory_sa_13';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '名字：云上天台',
  name_en = 'Cloud-top Rooftop',
  body = '<p>At ~380 m elevation, the wooden-decked platform offers unobstructed 360° views of the Yangtze and Jialing rivers, Yuzhong peninsula, Jiefangbei CBD, and on clear days, the Jinyun Mountain horizon.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_eling_2nd_factory_sa_14';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '名字：螺旋楼梯和涂鸦巷',
  name_en = 'Spiral Staircase & Graffiti Alley',
  body = '<p>Test Joy 街巷，形成"螺旋楼梯—涂鸦墙—Test Joy"的园区经典动线。 The 4-storey black-steel spiral staircase wraps a former silo, while the 80-metre alley beyond is painted by 12 Chinese graffiti artists with themes from Chongqing''s mountains, rivers and cyberpunk cityscape.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_eling_2nd_factory_sa_02';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '名字：巨型拉链雕塑',
  name_en = 'Giant Zipper Sculpture',
  body = '<p>A 7-metre-high brick wall pierced by a 6-metre stainless-steel zipper, installed in 2017 by a CAFA sculpture team. It symbolizes "unzipping industrial heritage for creative rebirth."</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_eling_2nd_factory_sa_03';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '名字：下沉广场',
  name_en = 'Sunken Plaza',
  body = '<p>Test Design 街巷与大门主入口，南通 Test Joy 街巷，西连 Test Spirit 街巷与 T² 艺术中心电梯，东侧则通过楼梯连接爱情天台与云上天台。广场中庭设置"老蒸汽机车头"实物（印钞厂运输遗留）与可移动座椅区，常年举办"鹅岭市集"周末市集及"二厂音乐现场"小型演出，是园区动线最密、节奏最快的核心节点。 Sunken 6 m into the original raw-material yard, the 1,800 sqm plaza links Test Design (north), Test Joy (south), Test Spirit (west) and the rooftop elevators (east). A preserved steam locomotive anchors the courtyard.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_eling_2nd_factory_sa_04';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '名字：重庆书局',
  name_en = 'Chongqing Bookstore',
  body = '<p>Test Spirit 街巷相连，是园区文化氛围最浓的"慢空间"。 A 1,200 sqm two-storey bookstore with 20,000+ titles, a Chongqing local-literature section, a design goods floor and a café—linked to Test Spirit Alley.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_eling_2nd_factory_sa_05';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '名字：你好童年怀旧馆',
  name_en = 'Hello Childhood Nostalgia Museum',
  body = '<p>An 800 sqm immersive nostalgia museum with thousands of 1970s–90s Chinese objects—enamel mugs, tin frogs, glass marbles, cassette games, and a recreated 1980s classroom with chalkboard desks.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_eling_2nd_factory_sa_06';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '名字：Test Spirit 街巷',
  name_en = 'Test Spirit Alley',
  body = '<p>Test Spirit 街巷位于园区西北部，由原印钞厂的 4 号、6 号仓库改造而成，整体氛围相对 Test Design 与 Test Joy 街巷更为安静、内敛。街巷两侧以木构、亚麻帘、绿植与原木家具为主，常驻品牌包括"彳亍"独立茶馆、"无用"中式香道馆、"素Yoga"瑜伽工作室与"拾光"二手书店等。这里也是园区最受欢迎的"放空发呆"角落——街巷尽头设有一面"鹅岭之眼"绿植墙和可席地而坐的阅读台阶，吸引大量摄影爱好者与文青静坐。 Converted from original warehouses 4 and 6, Test Spirit is the park''s quietest alley—lined with tea houses, incense studios, yoga spaces and the "Shiguang" second-hand bookshop. Its plant wall and reading steps form a favourite photo spot.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_eling_2nd_factory_sa_11';

UPDATE sub_areas SET
  name_zh = '名字：T²国际当代艺术中心',
  name_en = 'T² International Contemporary Art Center',
  body = '<p>T² 国际当代艺术中心位于园区 1 号楼顶层（部分延伸至 2 号楼），由原印钞厂办公楼改建而成，总面积约 1800 平方米，是鹅岭二厂文创公园的旗舰艺术机构。中心设有 1 个 800 平方米的主展厅、2 个 200 平方米的副展厅及艺术家驻地工作室群，由独立策展团队运营，自 2016 年开馆以来已举办"重庆身境""丝路镜像"等百余场当代艺术展。T² 长期与川美（虎溪）、重庆 501 艺术基地联动，是观察重庆当代艺术生态的窗口；展期内常配套艺术家对谈、工作坊与导览。 Occupying the top floors of the converted office Building 1, T² runs 1,800 sqm of exhibition space and residencies. It has staged over 100 contemporary shows since 2016 and partners with Sichuan Fine Arts Institute.</p>',
  updated_at = NOW()
WHERE id = 'chongqing_eling_2nd_factory_sa_12';
